get.description:
Opens a [Server-Sent Events](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events) stream that pushes one event named `message` each time mail arrives for this address. The event's `data` field is a JSON-encoded `MailEvent` (see the schema).

The stream sends periodic keep-alive comments to hold the connection open. It is a low-latency **nudge** only: events may be missed while disconnected and are not replayed, so on (re)connect always re-fetch `GET /api/addresses/{address}/messages` to reconcile.

Example (browser):

```js
const es = new EventSource(
  `/api/addresses/${encodeURIComponent(address)}/events`
);
es.addEventListener("message", (e) => {
  const evt = JSON.parse(e.data); // MailEvent
  // fetch the full message, or refresh the inbox listing
});
```

Note: this endpoint does not validate that the mailbox exists; subscribing to an unknown or expired address simply yields a stream that never emits.
